name: nonexistent paintings #001 - a painting of a burning police car
description:
text prompt: a painting of a burning police car
(single frame, 40 iterations per frame using VQGAN+CLIP)

this painting is the output of the thinking process of the following questions, "art according to what? / unified society according to who?". The output is created by intertwining the algorithm and the artistic input.

AI art creates synthetic media and maybe even democratizes “creativity”, by shifting the skillset from (graphical) execution or algorithmic instruction (programming) to nifty “prompt engineering”(by Max Woolf)
